Arsenal midfielder, Omari Hutchinson, is set to join Chelsea this summer as Manchester United’s deal for Lisandro Martinez has been revealed. According to football transfer expert Fabrizio Romano, Chelsea will soon announce a deal for Hutchinson, while Martinez will sign a contract with Man United that will see him remain at Old Trafford until 2027. Romano disclosed this in separate tweets via his Twitter handle on Friday. He tweeted, “Chelsea have signed another talent for the future. After Zak Sturge deal, Chelsea will soon announce Omari Hutchinson as new signing – he’s set to leave Arsenal.” “Talks collapsed with #AFC on a new deal, Hutchinson will join Chelsea as @TheSecretScout_reports. It’s done. “Lisandro Martínez to Manchester United, here we go! Full agreement in place between Man United and Ajax for package up to €55m. Lisandro will sign until 2027, documents now approved. “Deal done – meeting in Amsterdam on Wednesday was the key step. Ten Hag, big factor.”